author: COMSOL
description:
This example of turbulent flow in a partially baffled turbulent mixer shows how to set up The Rotating Machinery, Turbulent Flow interfaces from the Mixer Module with free surface and stationary free surface features. Both frozen rotor and time-dependent simulations are performed and compared.

NOTE: The model includes both a frozen-rotor and a time-dependent study, and can take about a day to solve. However, the frozen rotor study only takes a few hours to solve.
